Lesser Armor of the Wolf
This helm mounts two special crystal lenses over the wearer's eyes that grant a +5 bonus to Spot checks.

An unusual tradition in the mountainous village of Kale sprang up around 5 years ago, where villagers would take blunted arrows and fire them at each other in contests. Two lines would form up, with each person directly across from the other firing on command. Anyone not hit would remain, while all others backed out, until one person was left standing.
Travellers to the village reported the games were, "Marvellous fun to watch, but you'd have to be a bloody idiot to participate."
After a few years and several unfortunate deaths, the villagers went back to shooting at stuffed targets.

Several wars have sprung up between man and elf kind, since the discovery that humans were actually making these boots out of elves. The elves believe they have finally taught the humans how to make the boots properly from regular leather, but there is no underestimating the stupidity of some humans.

Blessed by priests of Calahi the god of merchants and travel, these boots seem to make even the most arduous journey easier and more pleasant. This is accomplished not by increasing the wearer's speed, but by making him hardier and more resistant to pain. Numerous versions of these boots exist, their power varying largely in accordance with the priest who blessed them.
Relics from the Age of the Magi, these bracers can still be found in the common gear of most adventurers. Anything that makes an adventurer quicker and harder to hit is a must-have item.

While these magical items have been around for thousands of years, their popularity never seems to decrease. Recently, a party of adventurers out of Delish uncovered a vast treasure trove, filled with magical items like these. The sudden influx of magical gauntlets does not seem to have decreased their value, as every adventurer across the land clamors for the assistance of these useful artifacts.

These cloaks of resistance are commonly found among the frost giant clans in the northern reaches of Valratha. 

The wearer can withstand extremes of cold weather and magical cold damage as well.

These bows seem primitive at first glance, but behind the crude sinew and hide is a powerful weapon. They are most often found in the far north of Valratha, but unfortunately, they are also most often found in the hands of one of the Cold Tongue orc raiders. Most observers will get a good look at the point of the arrows before ever seeing the bow.
Cold Tongue Bow
It is rumored that these rings were created in lands across the sea from Valratha. Since no ships have ever survived such a crossing of the seas, few believe these stories.
